{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17635447","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17635447"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:13:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:13:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17543"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17543","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17543"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0,0.29,0.11,0.57]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10233"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74637"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10233","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10233"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17543"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60131"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"2778"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"6107"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23932"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23935"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74637","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74637"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with difficulty walking and numbness in her right leg. She reports that she has been experiencing these symptoms for the past two weeks. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Neurological examination reveals weakness in plantar flexion of the ankle and toe flexion on the right side, along with decreased sensation in the posterior aspect of the right leg.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following nerves is most likely affected in this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Femoral nerve","Obturator nerve","Sciatic nerve","Superficial fibular nerve","Tibial nerve"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etibial nerve\u003C/strong\u003E is responsible for plantar flexion of the ankle and toe flexion, as well as providing sensation to the posterior leg and sole of the foot. The symptoms described in the stem, including weakness in plantar flexion and decreased sensation in the posterior leg, suggest an issue with the tibial nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be excluded for the following reasons:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u2022 \u003Cstrong\u003EFemoral nerve\u003C/strong\u003E: innervates the anterior thigh muscles and provides sensation to the anterior thigh and medial leg\u003Cbr /\u003E\u2022 \u003Cstrong\u003EObturator nerve\u003C/strong\u003E: innervates the medial thigh muscles and provides sensation to the medial thigh\u003Cbr /\u003E\u2022 \u003Cstrong\u003ESciatic nerve\u003C/strong\u003E: while it gives rise to the tibial nerve, the specific pattern of symptoms points more directly to isolated tibial nerve involvement\u003Cbr /\u003E\u2022 \u003Cstrong\u003ESuperficial fibular nerve\u003C/strong\u003E: innervates the muscles responsible for foot eversion and provides sensation to the dorsum of the foot\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The tibial nerve is responsible for plantar flexion of the ankle and toe flexion.","The tibial nerve provides sensation to the posterior leg and sole of the foot.","Understanding the function and sensory distribution of lower limb nerves is crucial for diagnosing nerve injuries."],"references":["Desai SS, Cohen-Levy WB. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Tibial Nerve. 2023 Aug 14. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725713.","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Merryman J, Varacallo M. Klumpke Palsy. 2023 Aug 4. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30285395","Garrett A, Geiger Z. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Calf Deep Peroneal Nerve (Deep Fibular Nerve). 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30252289"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60131"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17543"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60131","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60131"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T09:20:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T09:20:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10233"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74637"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","s